Selection Sort

Avg : Big O(n^2)


[2] [8] [5] [3] [9] [4] [1] 
↑↑ 
                                            
  __  __ __ __ __ __                    
 ↓   ↓   ↓   ↓   ↓    ↓  ↓
[2] [8] [5] [3] [9] [4] [1] 
 ↑______________________↑

       
[2] [8] [5] [3] [9] [4] [1]    
 ↑______________________↑
    
// the first index will try looking for a vallue lower than that
[1] [8] [5] [3] [9] [4] [2] 
    

SelectionSort(array)
    n = length(array)   
    for i from 0 to n-1       
        min_index = i
        for j from i+1 to n-1
            if array[j] < array[min_index]
                min_index = j
        if min_index != i
            swap(array[i], array[min_index])            
    return array
swap(a, b)
    temp = a
    a = b
    b = temp
